# 1. The correct planetary equation (core model)

The clean equation engineers actually use is:

[
N_s(\omega_s - \omega_c) + N_r(\omega_r - \omega_c) = 0
]

This is mathematically equivalent to Willis, but **much easier to solve**.

Expanded:

[
N_s\omega_s + N_r\omega_r = (N_s + N_r)\omega_c
]

From this we immediately get the **carrier speed formula**:

[
\omega_c =
\frac{N_s\omega_s + N_r\omega_r}{N_s + N_r}
]

This equation is **the safest implementation**.

